{
  "texts": [
    "Ma et al. (2025) distill a model-based verifier from a strong teacher and leverage it as a reward model to train a general reasoner without verifiers.",
    "Li et al. (2025) investigate large-scale multi-task RLVR, hypothesizing that breadth across many tasks induces stronger general reasoning.",
    "We build on this line of work while adopting a complementary perspective based on Inverse Reinforcement Learning.",
    "Inverse Reinforcement Learning (IRL) (Ng & Russell, 2000) studies the task of recovering a reward function for which an observed expert policy is near-optimal.",
    "A seminal application is robust imitation learning, most notably Generative Adversarial Imitation Learning (GAIL) (Ho & Ermon, 2016), casting imitation as an adversarial game between a policy and a discriminator."
  ]
}